---
import Layout from "../../../../layouts/index.astro"
---

<Layout>
	<p>
		Compares <code>operand</code> to <code>test</code> (an
		<code>Integer</code>) and returns a function that takes an optional
		<code>arg</code> and uses it as the operand or injects a argument from some other
		source (e.g., HTML element, query string, session storage).
	</p>
	<p>
		When called, the returned function returns the operand if it is
		more/less/etc. than the test number, otherwise returns an
		<code>Error</code>.
	</p>
	<p><strong>TODO</strong>: Extend to cover arrays.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>IsLength</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "String") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, String)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsLongerThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "String") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, String)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsNoLongerThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "String") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, String)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsNoShorterThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "String") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, String)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsNotLength</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "String") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, String)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsShorterThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "String") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, String)</code
			>
		</li>
	</ul>
</Layout>
